cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) architectures and their description using text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions data mining algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a unified approach for describing CNN architectures, which could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
